<HEAD>Eight Injured In Balcony Collapse</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 20-foot-high wooden balcony collapsed during
a Fourth of July party, injuring eight people, including a woman who
was impaled on a sprinkler pipe, authorities said.
   The woman, who was extricated after 30 minutes, and another woman
suffered critical injuries and were flown to UCLA Medical Center by
helicopter, said Fire Department spokesman Jim Williamson.
   Five others suffered minor injuries and were taken to hospitals.
One person refused treatment.
   The accident occurred Tuesday night while the people on the
balcony watched fireworks.
   ``It was a real frightening sound. I was hoping that it wasn't
what it was,'' said Risha Braun, who was directly above on a
third-floor balcony. ``I heard screams and the sound of (wood)
separation.''
