<SECOND>PM-Jail Brawl,0168</SECOND>
<HEAD>15 Inmates Injured in Fight in Jail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EL CAJON, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Black inmates wielding broom handles and
socks filled with soap bars attacked white prisoners in a cellblock
packed to five times its capacity, officials said. Fifteen inmates
were reported injured.
   The disturbance, which occurred Tuesday in a recreation area at
the El Cajon Detention Facility, continued sporadically for about 20
minutes before it was stopped by guards, sheriff's Sgt. Frank
Ramirez said.
   Fifteen black inmates started the melee in a sector designed for
24 inmates but holding 112, Ramirez said.
   Fifteen inmates were taken to the hospital with injuries
including concussions, a broken nose, cuts and bruises, officials
said. ``None of the injuries were life threatening, and there were
no injuries to the jail staff,'' Ramirez said.
   A series of disturbances in the San Diego County jails over the
past few months have been attributed to overcrowding, racial tension
and a no-smoking policy that took effect over the weekend.
