<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--FoodAid     07-05 0107</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Food Aid,0108</SECOND>
<HEAD>U.N. Food Aid Set for Lebanon, Malawi, Somalia, Uganda</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   More than $8 million in food aid will be provided for
displaced families in Lebanon, refugees in Malawi and Somalia, and
the hungry in Uganda, the U.N. World Food Program said Wednesday.
   The Rome-based agency said the aid will go to 50,000 displaced
families in Lebanon, 720,000 Mozambican refugees in Malawi and
600,000 Ethiopian refugees in Somalia.
   It will also provide aid to 600,000 people, including 30,000
malnourished children, in the West Nile region of Uganda, where
there have been food shortages and damage to the cassava crop, the
agency said.
</TEXT>
