<FIRST>r a AM-MarcosDaughter     07-05 0206</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Marcos Daughter,0211</SECOND>
<HEAD>Marcos Daughter: Inner Strength Keeping Former President Alive</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONOLULU (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former Philippine President Ferdinand Marcos'
inner strength is keeping him alive, but his family knows the end
could come at any time, says Marcos' daughter.
   ``Daddy has the capacity to strengthen us all,'' Irene Araneta
said Tuesday. ``The mere fact that he hasn't given up, we all know
it's the only thing that is keeping him alive.''
   Marcos was in very critical condition Wednesday, on life-support
machines and battling a widespread infection at St. Francis Medical
Center. He has been hospitalized since January. Doctors performed
surgery last week to remove his failed transplanted kidney.
   Mrs. Araneta, 28, Marcos' youngest child, said her family has had
several scares in recent months, but each time her father has
battled back.
   ``Each time we try to take it better. I guess it is like a
rehearsal,'' said Mrs. Araneta, a music student. ``I'm a great
believer in rehearsals. What are we rehearsing for? Well, it has to
come.
   ``We are still hopeful, prayerful, that it won't happen here. But
nobody knows if he is going to last until tomorrow.''
   Marcos was ousted in a 1986 civilian-military revolt that brought
President Corazon Aquino to power.
</TEXT>
