<HEAD>1 Dead, 1 Charged in Fireworks Explosion</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOUNT SINAI, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man was killed when a fireworks
explosion sent pieces of a cinderblock through the air, and the man
who set off the blast was charged with manslaughter, police said
Wednesday.
   The fireworks were placed on the cinderblock Tuesday night, and
the explosion caused pieces of the block to fly in different
directions, Suffolk County Sgt. Edward Fandry said.
   One piece hit John Connelly, 20, piercing his chest. Connelly, of
Yaphank, was taken to John Mather Memorial Hospital in Port
Jefferson, where he died.
   On Wednesday, police arrested Jeffrey DeFranco, 28, of Mount
Sinai on a charge of second-degreee manslaughter.
   Four other people who were hit by flying cinderblock pieces were
treated at a hospital and released, police and hospital officials
said.
