<FIRST>d a AM-WarholIndex     07-05 0216</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Warhol Index,0221</SECOND>
<HEAD>Counting Names in Warhol Diaries</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   If you guessed there were 2,335 names dropped in
``The Andy Warhol Diaries,'' you were close.
   The actual count is 2,338, according to Fame magazine, which
announced Wednesday it has compiled the first complete index to the
diaries and will publish same in its September issue.
   Until now, there has been no substitute for reading the entire
807-page book to find whether one's name was mentioned in Warhol's
diary of his social encounters from 1976 to 1987.
   ``With all that Andy had to say about so many people ... the one
thing that was clearly missing from the book was a complete and
comprehensive index,'' Fame editor-in-chief Gael Love said.
   Many of the names in the book were dropped dozens of times, Fame
found.
   Bianca Jagger got 84 mentions, the designer Halston 98 and artist
Jean-Michel Basqiuat topped that with 111. On the other end of the
scale, Yogi Berra, Idi Amin and Dick Tracy rated one mention apiece.
   The index will have the same page size as the book and will be
detachable so it can be inserted in the book, the announcement said.
``Diaries'' was No. 10 on the non-fiction best seller list in the
latest New York Times Book Review.
</TEXT>
