<FIRST>r i BC-Gorbachev-Text     07-05 0219</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Gorbachev-Text,0222</SECOND>
<HEAD>Text of Gorbachev-Mitterrand Declaration on Lebanon</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Gorbachev</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Text of the declaration of Soviet President Mikhail
S. Gorbachev and French President Francois Mitterrand, as translated
from French by The Associated Press:
   M.S. Gorbachev and F. Mitterrand expressed their profound
preoccupation with respect to the situation of persistent crisis in
Lebanon, as well as the misfortunes and sufferings of the Lebanese
population. They call for an immediate cease-fire, rigorously
respected, as an indispensable condition for the establishment of a
constructive inter-Lebanese dialogue, aiming at national
reconciliation and peaceful building of a country founded on a
balance of the interests of all Lebanese communities. They judge
also that these measures should be taken urgently to assure an end
to arms deliveries to any Lebanese group in conflict.
   While proclaiming their support for the mission of the
``committee of three'' of the Arab League on Lebanon, the U.S.S.R.
and France reiterated their availability to contribute by all means
to pacification efforts, and notably, in the framework of the United
Nations Security Council, in liaison with the mission it has
confided to the Secretary General.
   M.S. Gorbachev and F. Mitterrand are convinced that Lebanon must
remain a sovereign, independent, united, with its territorial
integrity respected, as well as a full and effective member of the
international community.''
</TEXT>
