<HEAD>Text of Decision by Likud Committee</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Israel-Politics</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TEL AVIV, Israel (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Text of the decision adopted by the
central committee of the Likud bloc at its meeting Wednesday, as
translated from Hebrew by The Associated Press (Judea and Samaria
are the terms Israelis often use to describe the occupied West Bank):
   The central committee approves the political announcement of the
prime minister at its meeting today ... the 5th of July 1989 and the
principles included in it, such as:
   _ The continuation of the peace process, according to the Camp
David agreements and the government's peace initiative;
   _ Non-participation of east Jerusalem Arabs in the elections;
