<FIRST>r w AM-NorthSentences     07-05 0144</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-North Sentences,130</SECOND>
<HEAD>Details of North's Sentences</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-North,000</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are the sentences meted out Wednesday by
U.S. District Judge Gerhard A. Gesell to Oliver North:
   For aiding abetting in the obstruction of Congress: 3 years,
suspended; probation two years, fine of $100,000.
   For altering, removing and destroying documents: 2 years,
suspended; probation two years, fine of $35,000. In addition, Gesell
said, ``I am required by the statute to impose another mandatory
penalty. You are hereby disqualified from holding any office under
the United States.''
   For receiving an illegal gratuity: One year, suspended; probation
two years, fine of $15,000.
   Gesell said the sentences and probation are to run concurrently,
while the fines are cumulative _ a total of $150,000. In addition,
Gesell imposed $50 penalties on each of the three sentences, money
that goes into the government's victim compensation funds.
