<FIRST>r i AM-Soviet-Hostage     07-05 0162</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Soviet-Hostage,0167</SECOND>
<HEAD>Soviets Rescue Woman Guard Taken Hostage at Prison</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three inmates at a Moscow prison took a female
guard hostage Wednesday, but she was freed a short time later by an
assault team, Tass said.
   ``An assault group performed a rescue operation with precision,
and made no mistakes,'' the official Soviet news agency said. It did
not give further details about the group.
   The team disarmed the criminals, who were threatening the woman
with crudely made knives, Tass said. The report did not say whether
shots were fired or whether anyone was hurt.
   The inmates were serving sentences for burglary, and the oldest
one was 18, Tass said. They grabbed the guard and threatened to kill
her if they were not freed and given a car, the news agency said.
   The inmates refused to negotiate, Tass said, so the assault team
went in 40 minutes after the standoff began at 11:20 a.m.
   Tass gave no other details.
</TEXT>
