<SECOND>BC-Dairy Sale,0142</SECOND>
<HEAD>Dairy Firm Sold To Irish Company</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FOND DU LAC, Wis. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Galloway West Co., a subsidiary of
Borden Inc. and Wisconsin's largest producer of Swiss cheese, is
being bought by Ireland's Waterford Foods PLC, Galloway announced
Wednesday.
   The purchase price was not disclosed.
   Galloway West will continue to do business under its current
name, and company spokesman Steven Carr said Galloway's 300
employees should not be affected by the transaction.
   Galloway West makes a variety of dairy products. Its New London
facility is the largest volume Swiss cheese plant in Wisconsin,
accounting for about 50 percent of the state's production.
   Waterford Foods is a major Irish food company and a leading
European manufacturer and marketer of dairy products, employing
about 1,200 people. The company had 1988 sales of approximately $330
million.
