<SECOND>BC-Britain-Stocks, 1st Ld-Writethru, f0022,0209</SECOND>
<HEAD>London Shares Close Lower</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: New thruout with closing figures.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices on the London Stock Exchange closed
lower Wednesday in light trading, skidding to the day's lows as
prices fell early in the session on Wall Street.
   At the close, the Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index
was down 11.5 points, or 0.5 percent, at 2,162.9.
   The narrower Financial Times 30-share index was down 1.5 points
at 1798.8.
   The Financial Times 500-share index closed at 1,231.58, down 4.46.
   Volume fell to 347.4 million shares compared with Tuesday's 373.2
million shares.
   Because of a transport strike, the third one-day stoppage in as
many weeks, the stock exchange closed one hour early to allow
traders and fund managers extra time to make their way home.
   The London market had been eagerly awaiting Wall Street's opening
Wednesday, the first day of trading following Tuesday's U.S.
Independence Day holiday.
   ``You've got a bit of a nothing market to start with. Then with
Wall Street coming in easier, it knocked (the London market down
further,'' said one dealer.
   On Wall Street, the Dow Jones Industrial Average was down about
15 points when the London trading session ended.
</TEXT>
